-- AnsaldoBreda, Bombardier Win Italian Contract for 50 High-Speed Trains
-- Marco Bertacche
-- 2010-08-02T16:48:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/ansaldobreda-bombardier-win-italian-contract-for-50-high-speed-trains.html

          
          
             Italy’s state-controlled railway
company said Finmeccanica SpA’s AnsaldoBreda unit and Canada’s
Bombardier Inc. won the bidding contest for 50 high-speed
trains, according to an e-mailed statement.  
 The official award will take place on Aug. 5, the statement
said.  
          
          


  


        